Wrap the ice cubes in a clean bar towel or hand towel. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/48/Make-a-Dragon-Martini-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Dragon-Martini-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/4/48/Make-a-Dragon-Martini-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/aid1900261-v4-728px-Make-a-Dragon-Martini-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Place the towel on a cutting board or other firm surface. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/de/Make-a-Dragon-Martini-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Dragon-Martini-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/d/de/Make-a-Dragon-Martini-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/aid1900261-v4-728px-Make-a-Dragon-Martini-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":327,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"518","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Hit the towel-wrapped ice with a wooden mallet until the ice has broken up into small pieces. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ca/Make-a-Dragon-Martini-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Dragon-Martini-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/c/ca/Make-a-Dragon-Martini-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/aid1900261-v4-728px-Make-a-Dragon-Martini-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":319,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"505","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
